  "doc_id": "19081",
  "text": "In summary, H372A works directly and locally at the binding pocket to simultaneously eliminate class I ligand binding and to promote class II ligand binding-the phenotype of direct switching. In contrast, G330T works allosterically to open up conformational plasticity at the binding pocket, which enables both class I and class II recognition-the phenotype of classbridging binding. It is important to note that this plasticity does not come in the form of general flexibility of the binding pocket reminiscent of low-affinity, broad-specificity interfaces, such as in the immature, germline isoforms of antibodies [CITATION_1] . Instead, it opens up just one additional macroscopic conformational state ( Figures 5F and 5G) , which results in highaffinity, dual-class ligand specificity ( Figure 3B ).",
